T1  - Stochastic inflation and the equity premium
AU  - Labadie, Pamela
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 24
IS  - 2
SP  - 277
EP  - 298
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/09/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(89)90007-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439328990007X
AB  - Stochastic inflation and the equity premium are studied in an asset-pricing endowment model with a cash-in-advance constraint. Inflation affects the equity premium through the inflation tax and the inflation risk premium. The equity premium in both the monetary model and the real model - a continuous state-space generalization of Mehra and Prescott (1985) - is sensitive to the conditional variance of the endowment growth. When the standard deviation is increased from 3.49% to 5.59%, the real model generates an equity premium of 2.8% in the relevant range of risk aversion parameters; the monetary model generates an equity premium of 5.81%.
